        {
            "id": "https://cazzola.click/hamer-time.html",
            "url": "https://cazzola.click/hamer-time.html",
            "title": "Hammer Time",
            "summary": "<h5>Details:</h5>\n<h6></h6>\n<h6></h6>\n<ul>\n<li>A 2D game inspired by Ikaruga.</li>\n<li>8 week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 3 level designers and 4 artists. Game project 3 at The Game Assembly.</li>\n<li>Made in TGA2D, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</li>\n</ul>\n<h5>My contibutions:</h5>\n<ul>\n<li>Player movement.</li>\n<li>Xbox and keyboard input manager.</li>\n<li>Sprite sheet based animations.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AQroTOqMwWY?start=15&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\n",
            "content_html": "<h5>Details:</h5>\n<h6></h6>\n<h6></h6>\n<ul>\n<li>A 2D game inspired by Ikaruga.</li>\n<li>8 week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 3 level designers and 4 artists. Game project 3 at The Game Assembly.</li>\n<li>Made in TGA2D, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</li>\n</ul>\n<h5>My contibutions:</h5>\n<ul>\n<li>Player movement.</li>\n<li>Xbox and keyboard input manager.</li>\n<li>Sprite sheet based animations.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AQroTOqMwWY?start=15&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\n\n<h5>Spritesheet based animations:</h5>\n<p>During the project, I had to develop a pipeline for importing sprite sheets into the TGA2D game engine. I came up with a solution where the artist used <a href=\"https://www.codeandweb.com/texturepacker\">TexturePacker </a>to export the sprite sheet and a JSON file that described the coordinates of each sprite. I then created a pipeline that could read the JSON file and develop an animation system capable of switching between different animations.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/sheet_game_crop.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"4081\" height=\"1351\" sizes=\"(min-width: 37.5em) 1600px, 80vw\" srcset=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-xs.png 384w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-sm.png 600w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-md.png 768w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-lg.png 1200w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-xl.png 1600w\"></figure>",
